<p>The delivery of a condolence text also requires careful consideration. Timeliness is key; sending a message promptly shows your immediate concern. Keep the message concise and heartfelt, avoiding lengthy explanations or unsolicited advice.  Ensure your message is free of grammatical errors and typos, reflecting the seriousness of the occasion.  Above all, let your genuine compassion shine through every word.</p>
    

